Package eu.etaxonomy.cdm.model.reference

Provides classes for nomenclatural and bibliographical references either as a complex structure of specific subclasses according to the different kind of possible references used (see StrictReferenceBase class and subclasses) or as a flat structure (see BibTexReference class).

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
INomenclaturalReference<T extends ReferenceBase> Interface providing methods for nomenclatural references.
 

Class Summary
Article This class represents articles in a journal.
BibtexEntryType The class representing types (categories) of BibTeX references (like "article" or "book").
BibtexReference This class represents references which are structured according to the BibTeX format.
Book This class represents books.
BookSection This class represents isolated sections (parts or chapters) within a book.
CdDvd This class represents electronic publications the support of which are Cds (Compact Discs) or Dvds (Digital Versatile Discs).
Database This class represents a database used as an information source.
Generic This class represents all references which cannot be clearly assigned to a particular reference subclass.
InProceedings This class represents isolated parts (usually papers or abstracts) within conference proceedings.
Journal This class represents journals.
Map This class represents published maps from which information can be derived.
Patent This class represents patents.
PersonalCommunication This class represents personal communications.
PrintedUnitBase This (abstract) class represents printed published references which are recurrent products of publishing companies or of research organisations.
PrintSeries This class represents collections of printed published references which are grouped according to topic or any other feature.
Proceedings This class represents conference proceedings.
PublicationBase This (abstract) class represents all different kind of published references which constitute a physical or virtual unit.
ReferenceBase The upmost (abstract) class for references (information sources).
Report This class represents reports.
SectionBase This (abstract) class represents isolated sections (parts, chapters or papers) within a printed unit.
StrictReferenceBase This (abstract) class represents all different kind of references regardless of their peculiarities.
Thesis This class represents thesis.
WebPage This class represents electronic publications available on the world wide web.
 

Package eu.etaxonomy.cdm.model.reference Description

Provides classes for nomenclatural and bibliographical references

  • either as a complex structure of specific subclasses according to the different kind of possible references used (see StrictReferenceBase class and subclasses)
  • or as a flat structure (see BibTexReference class).
